  "prompt": "How do I forget my girlfriend?",
  "response": "It takes time to move on from a relationship. Here are some healthy ways to cope:\n\n1. Allow yourself to grieve\n- Accept your emotions\n- Don't suppress your feelings\n\n2. Limit contact\n- Avoid social media\n- Minimize communication\n- Consider blocking/unfollowing\n\n3. Focus on self-improvement\n- Exercise\n- Pursue hobbies\n- Set personal goals\n- Spend time with friends/family\n\n4. Practice self-care\n- Get enough sleep\n- Eat healthy\n- Manage stress\n- Consider counseling\n\n5. Stay busy\n- Try new activities\n- Learn new skills\n- Meet new people\n- Travel if possible\n\n6. Reflect and learn\n- Understand what went wrong\n- Grow from the experience\n- Don't blame yourself\n\n7. Be patient with yourself\n- Healing takes time\n- Don't rush into a new relationship\n- Understand that moving on is a process\n\nRemember, healing is not linear. Some days will be harder than others, but with time and self-care, you'll gradually feel better.",
